==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bower-Barff process
<hw>Bow"er-Barff" proc`ess</hw> . <fld>(Metal.)</fld> <def>A certain
process for producing upon articles of iron or steel an adherent coating
of the magnetic oxide of iron (which is not liable to corrosion by air,
moisture, or ordinary acids). This is accomplished by producing, by
oxidation at about 1600⟦deg⟧ F. in a closed space, a coating containing
more or less of the ferric oxide (<chform>Fe2O3</chform>) and the
subsequent change of this in a reduced atmosphere to the magnetic oxide
(<chform>Fe2O4</chform>).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bower bird</ent>⟦br⟧
